                            <h2>Company Areas, Subcommittees and Nodes</h2>

                            <ol>
                                <li value="8">TheGoodData is divided into four major Areas of responsibility: Corporate (strategy, finance, legal &amp; brand), Product (development of different projects and operations), Data (harvesting, securing, processing and trading) and People (users, members, collaborators and social impact). Each of these Areas will be lead by a Director. The major decisions of each Area will be raised to the Board of Directors for approval. </li>
                                <li>Directors may decide to appoint an Area Subcommittee to provide support for the company’s day-to-day duties. Subcommittees are made-up of three people and shall comprise one Director or a Director elected Officer and two other Members for a duration of one year. At least two of these individuals should participate in major decisions.</li>
                                <li>The proceedings of Subcommittee meetings are to be reported to the Board of Directors. Subcommittee meetings may make decisions on affairs relating to the work of the particular Area, but issues of direct importance to the TheGoodData as a whole should be taken, as a proposal or item for discussion, to the Board of Directors. The Directors may open for discussion decisions made at Subcommittee meetings if it is deemed that they are of direct importance to the TheGoodData as a whole.</li>
                                <li>The Membership Subcommittee will be in charge, among other duties. of accepting Membership applications, dealing with Member claims, evaluating Member’s expulsion cases, or disclosing any Member’s data if requested by authorities. 

                                    <ol type="a">
                                        <li> Subcommittee Members aside from a Director or elected Officer will be elected by the rest of the Members, preferably at the Annual General Meeting</li>
                                        <li> If the Board considers that the volume of work, or language diversity, so justifies, they are empowered to establish more than one Membership Subcommittee.</li>
                                        <li>Membership applications and claims can be dealt by one single (1) Subcommittee Member.</li> 
                                        <li> In case of unresolved claims, the Member should raise the matter with the designated Board Member. If the matter is not resolved informally, the Member should write to the Board so that the matter can be raised at the next Board meeting.</li>
                                        <li> Member expulsion decisions will only be made after inviting the Member to submit written comments about the case.</li>
                                        <li> Disclosure to Authorities of Membership Data can only be done upon approval of the majority of Subcommittee Members. The Subcommittee will only attend to requests from legitimate authorities.</li>
                                        <li>Subcommittee Members shall, prior to acceptance of their duties, read and accept TheGoodData’s Privacy Policy and commit to enforce it at all times.</li>
                                    </ol>
                                <li>Subcommittees for the other Areas can be appointed at any time by the Area Director who will determine their Membership.</li>
                                <li>Ad hoc working &ldquo;Nodes&rdquo; may be appointed by the Board of Directors at any time to deal with cross-area projects like the development of a new service or business line.</li>
                            </ol>

                            <h2> Conduct of Meetings</h2>
                            <ol>
                                <li value="14">The following rules apply to day-to-day meetings including Board Meetings, Subcommittee and Node Meetings. The Provision and Procedure for General Meetings is outlined in the Company Rules.</li>
                                <li>All meetings should have an agenda and a determined duration. The date of the next meeting shall be agreed at each meeting.</li>
                                <li>Meetings should always be minuted and mention the meeting attendants, major decisions made, actions identified, owners and deadlines. Minutes will be distributed among attendants prior to the next meeting and will be made available online to all members - excluding parts subject to TheGoodData’s Privacy Policy - except if the Board of Directors declares it confidential.</li>
                                <li>Members who are absent from a meeting may, in advance, voice an opinion and cast a vote on any or all of the items on the agenda.</li>
                                <li>An unjustified absence of two consecutive meetings, or a justified absence of over 50% of meetings over a three-month period but without extraordinary circumstances, may be held by the rest of the meeting Members to elect a substitute.</li>
                                <li>Decisions are to be made by a majority.</li>
                                <li> Volunteers, and any such persons that the Members of the meeting wish to invite, in an advisory or observational role, may attend meetings. Members who wish to attend should contact any meeting Member in advance, and be granted permission unless their attendance is deemed inappropriate. Meeting attendees may speak by request/with the permission of any of the meeting Members.</li>
                                <li> Both day-to-day and General Meetings, as well as any other communication between TheGoodData and its Members, including calls for meetings and circulation of meeting minutes, will be done electronically.</li>
                            </ol>

                            <h2 > Application of income and surplus</h2>
                            <ol>
                                <li value="22">A share of revenues not lower than 10% will be invested in the support of not-for-profit causes unless TheGoodData viability is placed in danger due to this investment.</li>
                                <li>Starting from the second year of TheGoodData operations, one sixth of revenues will be given to external developers that have collaborated in building TheGoodData systems, code and algorithms during the previous six years. Sharing criteria will be decided by the Product Area Director or Product Subcommittee, and will consider the level of effort (ie. lines of code), the quality of the output and the strategic importance of the development.</li>
                                <li>Our Company Rules allow us to distribute surplus to Members as dividends; however we have chosen at present not to exercise this option, since we seek to strengthen the long-term viability of our organisation and further our social impact.</li>
                            </ol>
                            <h2 > Data asset lock</h2>
                            <ol>
                                <li value="25">If we should ever file for bankruptcy or have any of our assets sold to or merged with another entity, data that we have harvested or processed of our users will never be transferred, nor will be the browser extensions that we have made available through the various app stores.</li>
                            </ol>

                            <h2 > Changes to these rules</h2>
                            <ol>
                                <li value="26">These Secondary Rules are evolving and may be changed by the Board as long as they are not in conflict with the Company Rules. Any agreed changes need to be confirmed at a General Meeting and agreed by the majority of Members.</li>
                            </ol>
                            
                            
                            <p>First drafted &ndash; May 2014</p>
                            <p>Latest revision &ndash; May 2014 </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane legal" id="principles">
                            <h1>TheGoodData Principles</h1>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="title">Data Ownership</div>
                                <div class="description"><strong>People are the only owners of the data they produce</strong>. This means that they must be aware of its existence, that they can freely decide who should have access to it and set the terms and benefits to be received in exchange. All these decisions should be presented to the people in an easy and understandable way.</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="title">Optimism</div>
                                <div class="description"><strong>By ensuring Data ownership, Customers will be happier</strong>. Customers will gain freedom of choice, a more balanced position when dealing with corporations, and a higher value in exchange for the data they decide to share, if any. Data can therefore be Good for Customers.</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="title">Collaboration</div>
                                <div class="description"><strong>Collaboration among customers is the only way to fully achieve data ownership</strong> since Corporations and Administrations have many competing interests. TheGoodData is an expression of this collaboration. </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="title">Openness</div>
                                <div class="description"><strong>Openness facilitates collaboration of both Customers and Coders</strong>, and therefore the development of more and better products. TheGoodData will to the best of its ability ensure that all its actions, decisions and assets are transparent and open to participation.</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="title">Individual choice</div>
                                <div class="description">While being a collaborative initiative <strong>it's always upon the Customer to decide what to do as an individual with his/her own data</strong>. Individuals should therefore always be entitled to cease all relations with TheGoodData,export the data that they have created and eliminate it from TheGoodData databases.</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="title">Protection</div>
                                <div class="description"><strong>Data ownership can only be assured with full Data protection</strong>. TheGoodData will always implement most robust legal and technical measures to ensure anonymity and avoid unwanted access to data by unauthorised individuals, corporations and administrations. TheGoodData also expects that its Users and Members to be diligent in this regard. </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="title">Social Good</div>
                                <div class="description"><strong>TheGoodData believes that its Mission can be achieved while at the same time contributing positively to sociey</strong>. Thus, it will always take into consideration the social impact of its actions.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
<script>    $(function() {
        // sets the acive tab
        var url = $(location).attr('href'),
        indexOfHash = url.lastIndexOf('#'),
        idInUrl = (indexOfHash < 0)?'':url.substr(indexOfHash);
        
        if(idInUrl){
            var activeHref = $('.nav-tabs li.active a').attr('href');
            if (activeHref != idInUrl){
                // remove class
                $('.nav-tabs li.active').removeClass('active');
                $('.tab-pane.active').removeClass('active');
            
                // add class
                $('.nav-tabs li').find('[href=' + idInUrl + ']').parent().addClass('active');
                $(idInUrl).addClass('active');
            }
        }      
        
        // scrolls the page to an inner-link 
        $(".inner-link").click(function() {
            var reference = "." + $(this).data('ref'),
                    initialScroll = $(reference).find(".tab-pane.active").scrollTop(),
                    offsetHref = $("#" + $(this).data("target")).offset().top,
                    offsetRef = $(reference).offset().top,
                    deltaOffset = offsetHref - offsetRef;

            $(reference).find(".tab-pane.active").animate({
                scrollTop: initialScroll + deltaOffset
            }, 1000);
            return false;
        });
        setTimeout(function(){
            window.scrollTo(0,0);
        },200);
    });
    
</script>